The paper focuses on understanding and visualizing mode collapse in Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and proposes a framework to analyze GANs trained on multiple datasets. This work involves computer vision (CV) techniques such as semantic segmentation and image inversion, as well as machine learning (ML) concepts such as GANs and deep learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also deals with ML models and their training, which suggests the sub-category cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves AI techniques such as generative models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with graphics and visualization, which could fall under cs.GR (Graphics). Finally, the paper involves image processing and manipulation, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
